'''Unai Simón Mendibil''' (born 11 June 1997) is a Spanish [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Spanish football updater|Athletic Bilbao}} club [[Athletic Bilbao]] and the [[Spain national football team|Spain national team]].

Simón has spent his entire club career with Athletic, developing with their youth academy, farm team and reserves and making his senior debut in 2018, amassing 200 appearances by 2025.

Simón made his senior international debut for Spain in 2020 and played at [[UEFA Euro 2020]], the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], and [[UEFA Euro 2024]], where he featured in all but one match as Spain won the latter tournament.

==Early life==
Simón's father, a member of the [[Guardia Civil]] from the [[Province of Zamora]], was assigned to a security posting in the [[Basque Country (autonomous community)|Basque Country]] where he met Unai's mother, a member of the [[Ertzaintza]] (the local police force);<ref name=":1">{{cite web |last=Galiacho |first=Juan Luís |date=18 June 2023 |title=Unai Simón: El portero vasco hijo de un Guardia Civil y una ertzaina lleva a la Selección española al triunfo |trans-title=Unai Simón: The Basque goalkeeper, son of a Civil Guard leads the Spanish National Team to victory |url=https://elcierredigital.com/pizarra-deportiva/unai-simon-portero-vasco-hijo-guardia-civil-y-ertzaina |access-date=10 January 2024 |website=El Cierre Digital |language=es}}</ref> their son was born in [[Vitoria-Gasteiz]], [[Álava]], and raised in the nearby village of [[Murgia (Álava)|Murgia]].<ref name="Pueblo">{{cite web|url=https://elpais.com/deportes/eurocopa-futbol/2021-07-04/el-pueblo-de-mikel-landa-ya-es-el-pueblo-de-unai-simon.html?outputType=amp|title=El pueblo de Mikel Landa ya es el pueblo de Unai Simón|trans-title=Mikel Landa's village is now Unai Simón's village |publisher=[[El País]] |language=es|date=4 July 2021|access-date=9 January 2022}}</ref>

He joined [[Athletic Bilbao]]'s youth system in 2011 from [[CD Aurrerá de Vitoria|Aurrerá Vitoria]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lacanteradelezama.com/entrevista-a-unai-simon/|title=Entrevista a Unai Simon|trans-title=Interview to Unai Simon|website=La Cantera de Lezama|language=es|date=11 July 2015|access-date=18 July 2017}}</ref> lodging with a family in the [[Bilbao]] area.<ref name=":1" />

==Club career==
Simón made his debut as a senior with [[CD Basconia|Basconia]], Athletic's [[farm team]], in the [[2014–15 Tercera División|2014–15 season]], in the [[Tercera División]].<ref name=":2">{{cite web |title=Unai Simón |url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/players/unai-simon-mendibil |website=Athletic Bilbao |access-date=25 October 2021}}</ref> On 8 June 2016, he was promoted to [[Bilbao Athletic|the reserves]], [[2015–16 Segunda División|recently relegated]] to the [[Segunda División B]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/16822/leaving-basconia.html|title=Leaving Basconia|publisher=Athletic Bilbao|date=8 June 2016|access-date=18 July 2017|archive-date=21 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821031958/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/16822/leaving-basconia.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He immediately became a starter for the side, contributing with 29 appearances during [[2016–17 Segunda División B|the campaign]].<ref name=":2" />

On 2 June 2017, he was called up to the main squad for the pre-season by new first team manager [[José Ángel Ziganda]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/17960/preseason-with-the-premier-team.html|title=Preseason with the premier team|publisher=Athletic Bilbao|date=2 June 2017|access-date=18 July 2017|archive-date=21 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180821031906/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/17960/preseason-with-the-premier-team.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> but continued to appear exclusively for the B-team. On 13 July 2018, he signed a contract extension until 2023,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/19190/renewal-of-unai-simon.html|title=Renewal of Unai Simón|publisher=Athletic Bilbao|date=13 July 2018|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=20 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820235131/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/19190/renewal-of-unai-simon.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> and was loaned to [[Segunda División]] side [[Elche CF|Elche]] two weeks later.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/19230/unai-simon-on-loan-to-elche-cf.html|title=Unai Simón on-loan to Elche CF|publisher=Athletic Bilbao|date=27 July 2018|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=20 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820234912/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/19230/unai-simon-on-loan-to-elche-cf.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 15 August 2018, after [[Kepa Arrizabalaga]]'s departure from the club and [[Iago Herrerín]]'s injury, Simón was recalled by Athletic before he had played a match for Elche.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/19288/recovery-of-unai-simon.html|title=Recovery of Unai Simón|publisher=Athletic Bilbao|date=15 August 2018|access-date=20 August 2018|archive-date=20 August 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180820235156/https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/19288/recovery-of-unai-simon.html|url-status=dead}}</ref> He initially appeared to be behind the older [[Álex Remiro]] in the queue for selection,<ref>{{cite web |last=Ortiz de Lazcano |first=Javier |date=8 August 2018 |title=La salida de Kepa facilita la continuidad de Remiro |trans-title=Kepa's departure makes it easier for Remiro to continue |url=https://www.elcorreo.com/athletic/salida-kepa-facilitara-20180808223557-nt.html |access-date=11 February 2019 |website=[[El Correo]] |language=es}}</ref> but made his professional – and [[La Liga]] – debut five days later, starting in a 2–1 home win against [[CD Leganés|Leganés]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marca.com/en/football/spanish-football/2018/08/21/5b7b3ce422601d0f4f8b4646.html|title=Muniain gives Berizzo his first win as Athletic Club coach|publisher=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]]|last1=García|first1=Óscar|date=21 August 2018|access-date=21 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Zubieta |first=Jon |date=21 August 2018 |title=Simón debuta con un paradón providencial |trans-title=Simón debuts with a providential save |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20180821/451393160369/athletic-unai-simon-remiro-porteria-san-mames.html |access-date=21 August 2018 |website=[[Mundo Deportivo]] |language=es}}</ref> In just his third appearance in the top division, Simón played in a 1–1 draw with [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] where he made several key saves and was named player of the match.<ref>{{cite web|title=Isco goal salvages point for Real Madrid away to Athletic Bilbao|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/liga/2018-2019/isco-goal-salvages-point-for-real-madrid-away-to-athletic-bilbao_sto6932432/story.shtml|date=15 September 2018|access-date=19 September 2018|first=Graham|last=Ruthven|publisher=[[Eurosport]]}}</ref> However, when Herrerín regained full fitness in October 2018 he was made the starting goalkeeper, with Simón's only appearances over the subsequent four months coming in the [[Copa del Rey]].<ref name=":2" />

For the [[2019–20 Athletic Bilbao season|2019–20 season]], Simón was given the No. 1 squad number and began the campaign as first choice, keeping a clean sheet in an opening day win over [[FC Barcelona|Barcelona]].<ref>{{cite news |date=17 August 2019 |title=Athletic Bilbao 1–0 Barcelona: Aritz Aduriz hits spectacular winner |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49371762 |access-date=26 August 2019 |work=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> He continued his strong form throughout the season, missing two fixtures with illness and completing 33 matches in the league, conceding 29 goals<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bdfutbol.com/en/p/j22117.html?cat=1a&temp=2019-20&equip=6&rival=-&jug=-|title=Matches Unai Simón (filters: 2019-20 season, La Liga, Athletic Club) |website=BDFutbol|access-date=17 July 2020 }}</ref> to finish third in the [[Ricardo Zamora Trophy|Zamora Trophy]] rankings.<ref>{{cite web |title=Trofeo Zamora de LaLiga EA Sports 2024 - 2025 - Mejor portero Primera División |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/zamora.html |access-date=4 September 2020 |website=[[Marca (newspaper)|Marca]] |language=es}}</ref> On the 37th, penultimate, matchday, he was sent off during the first half against Leganés for a 'last man' challenge outside the penalty area, with the resultant suspension ending his season a game early; with ten men, Athletic Bilbao lost 2–0 to end their slim hopes of qualifying for the [[UEFA Europa League]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cdleganes.com/en/new/leganes-wins-against-athletic-at-san-mames-and-is-still-alive-0-2|title=Leganés wins against Athletic at San Mamés and is still alive (0-2)|publisher=CD Leganés|date=16 July 2020|access-date=17 July 2020|archive-date=19 July 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200719032330/https://www.cdleganes.com/en/new/leganes-wins-against-athletic-at-san-mames-and-is-still-alive-0-2|url-status=dead}}</ref>

In August 2020, he signed a new contract with the club running to the summer of 2025, with no buyout clause.<ref>{{cite web |title=Unai Simón renews contract until 2025 |url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2020/08/20/unai-simon-renews-contract-until-2025 |date=20 August 2020|website=Athletic Club |access-date=21 February 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Unai Simon signs five-year Athletic deal with no release clause |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/unai-simon-signs-five-year-athletic-deal-with-no-release-clause-30773244 |access-date=11 April 2025 |website=[[OneFootball]]}}</ref> In January 2021, he saved a penalty from [[Getafe CF|Getafe]]'s [[Jaime Mata]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Herrán |first=Alfonso |date=25 January 2021 |title=Raúl y Muniain, los superleones |trans-title= Raúl and Muniain, the super-lions |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/01/25/primera/1611611735_007974.html |access-date=9 April 2024 |website=[[Diario AS]] |language=es}}</ref> The following month he had a decisive role in the quarter-finals of the Copa del Rey, stopping two of the three penalties in the shootout at the [[Estadio Benito Villamarín]] against [[Real Betis]].<ref>{{cite web |date=5 February 2021 |title=Unai Simón detiene dos penaltis y conduce el Athletic a semifinales |trans-title= Unai Simón saves two penalties and leads Athletic to the semifinals |url=https://www.elmundo.es/deportes/futbol/copa-del-rey/2021/02/05/601c7dc8fc6c83bf768b466f.html |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=ELMUNDO |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Espina |first=José A. |date=4 February 2021|title=Heroico Unai Simón |trans-title= Heroic Unai Simón |url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/02/04/copa_del_rey/1612472240_437875.html |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=[[Diario AS]] |language=es}}</ref>

During the 2021–22 season, he kept his place in the starting lineup and had several impressive performances, the most notable being against [[Levante UD|Levante]] and Getafe (both matches ending goalless).<ref>{{cite web |last=Burgos |first=Julián |date=19 November 2021 |title=Unai Simón le niega el triunfo al Levante en medio del diluvio |trans-title= Unai Simón denies Levante the victory in the midst of the deluge|url=https://as.com/futbol/2021/11/19/primera/1637360505_858993.html |access-date=9 April 2024 |website=[[Diario AS]] |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Rivas |first=Jon |date=6 December 2021 |title=Unai Simón frustra al Getafe |trans-title= Unai Simón frustrates Getafe |url=https://elpais.com/deportes/2021-12-06/unai-simon-frustra-al-getafe.html |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=El País |language=es}}</ref> In the following season, with the arrival of [[Ernesto Valverde]], he maintained his role as an undisputed starter in the league and performed at a good level.<ref>{{cite web |last=Herrán |first=Alfonso |date=11 February 2023 |title=El enésimo recital de Simón |trans-title= Simón's umpteenth recital|url=https://as.com/futbol/simon-se-exhibe-en-mestalla-n/ |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=Diario AS |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Aramendia |first=Arkaitz |date=13 February 2023 |title=Unai Simón, los datos de un muro en la portería del Athletic |trans-title=Unai Simón, the data of a wall in the Athletic goal |url=https://www.deia.eus/athletic/2023/02/13/unai-simon-datos-muro-porteria-6437418.html |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=Deia |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=13 February 2023 |title=Unai Simón es un número 1 |trans-title= Unai Simón is a Number 1|url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/athletic-bilbao/20230213/1001940117/unai-simon-numero-1.html |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=Mundo Deportivo |language=es}}</ref> On 10 November 2023, in "one of his best moments as a professional",<ref>{{cite web |last=Markinez |first=Iñigo |date=30 October 2023 |title=¿Está Unai Simón en el mejor momento de su carrera deportiva? |trans-title= Is this Unai Simón in the best moment of his sporting career? |url=https://cadenaser.com/euskadi/2023/10/30/esta-unai-simon-en-el-mejor-momento-de-su-carrera-deportiva-radio-bilbao/ |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=cadena SER |language=es}}</ref> he saved a penalty from [[Celta de Vigo|Celta Vigo]] striker [[Iago Aspas]] to keep the score level in a game his team went on to win.<ref>{{cite web |date=11 November 2023 |title=El Athletic se abraza a Simón y Nico, que llegan lanzados a la Selección |trans-title=Athletic embraces Simón and Nico, who are thrown into the National Team |url=https://www.relevo.com/futbol/liga-primera/athletic-abraza-simon-nico-llegan-20231111015912-nt.html |access-date=9 April 2024 |website=Relevo |language=es}}</ref> On 16 March 2024, he stopped another penalty from [[Luis Rioja]] of [[Deportivo Alavés|Alavés]], starting a move which culminated in a goal for Athletic forty seconds later as they again went on to win;<ref>{{cite web |date=16 March 2024|title=El Athletic duerme en Champions |trans-title=Athletic sleeps in the Champions League |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/primera-division/cronica/2024/03/16/65f5ee3722601d2c3e8b457f.html |access-date=9 April 2024  |website=MARCA |language=es}}</ref> in addition, he consolidated his position as leader in the Zamora Trophy with his 15th clean sheet in the league.<ref>{{cite web |date=17 March 2024 |title=Simón consolida el mejor momento de su carrera y aspira a su primer Zamora |trans-title=Simón consolidates the best moment of his career and aspires to his first Zamora |url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/athletic/2024/03/17/65f6d036e2704e7a9a8b45ad.html |access-date=9 April 2024|website=MARCA |language=es}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=16 March 2024 |title=Unai Simón da alas al Athletic |trans-title=Unai Simón gives wings to Athletic |url=https://www.mundodeportivo.com/futbol/laliga/20240316/1002210757/unai-simon-da-alas-athletic.html |access-date=9 April 2024 |website=Mundo Deportivo |language=es}}</ref> Having been the starter for Copa del Rey final defeats in [[2020 Copa del Rey final|2020]] and [[2020 Copa del Rey final|2021]], he played no active part as the club [[2024 Copa del Rey final|finally won the trophy in April 2024]], watching from the bench as understudy [[Julen Agirrezabala]] was selected for all rounds of the tournament. At the end of the season, Simón extended his contract to 2029.<ref>{{cite web |title=Athletic Club seal new deal for key player until 2029 |url=https://www.football-espana.net/2024/05/24/athletic-club-seal-new-deal-for-key-player-until-2029/ |date=24 May 2024|website=Football España }}</ref>

In October 2024, Simón was ranked in second place for the [[Yashin Trophy]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=28 October 2024|title=Aston Villa and Argentina goalkeeper Emiliano Martinez retains Yashin Trophy as world's best goalkeeper in 2024|url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/aston-villa-and-argentina-goalkeeper-emiliano-martinez-retains-yashin-trophy-as-world-s-best-goalkeeper-in-2024/blt47f77564722f26b5 |access-date=9 December 2024 |website=Goal.com}}</ref> He was unavailable for the first four months of the [[2024–25 Athletic Bilbao season|2024–25 season]] due to rehabilitation after surgery on his wrist, which was carried out immediately after the Euros tournament ended.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 November 2024|title=Unai Simon confirms availability for Basque derby after four-month injury absence|url=https://www.football-espana.net/2024/11/20/unai-simon-confirms-availability-for-basque-derby-after-four-month-injury-absence |access-date=9 December 2024 |website=Goal.com}}</ref> He made his 200th appearance for Athletic Bilbao in January 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Unai Simón reaches 200 appearances with Athletic Club |url=https://www.athletic-club.eus/en/news/2025/01/19/unai-simon-reaches-200-appearances-with-athletic-club/ |date=19 January 2025|website=Athletic Club }}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Unai Simón Mendibil.jpg|thumb|Simón with Spain youth team in 2015]]

===Youth===
Simón was selected for [[Spain national under-19 football team|Spain]] at [[Spain national football team|under-19]] and [[Spain national under-21 football team|under-21]] levels. He was a member of the squad that won the [[2015 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]], albeit as the backup goalkeeper to [[Antonio Sivera]] during the tournament.<ref name=sub19>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bidebietairratia.com/noticias/basauri/2015/07/22/el-portero-del-basconia-unai-simon-gana-el-europeo-sub-19-con-espana/|title=El portero del Basconia Unai Simón gana el Europeo sub'19 con España|trans-title=Basconia goalkeeper Unai Simón wins the U19 European Championship with Spain|last=Villapun|first=Jon|date=22 July 2015|website=Bidebieta|language=es|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> In the same year he was in the [[Basque Country national football team|Basque Country under-18 team]] that won the {{ill|Spanish regional championship|es|Campeonato de España de selecciones autonómicas de fútbol}}.<ref name="Pueblo"/>

On 1 September 2017, Simón debuted with the under-21 team against [[Italy national under-21 football team|Italy]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/seleccion/2017/09/01/59a9b49546163fb7378b4583.html|title=Selección de España: España da un repaso a Italia|trans-title=Spanish national team: Spain reviews Italy|date=1 September 2017|newspaper=Marca|language=es|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref> He was selected for the [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship]], playing the first game of the group stage as Spain once more finished as champions (Sivera was again first-choice).<ref>{{Cite magazine|url=https://www.marca.com/futbol/europeo-sub-21/cronica/2019/06/30/5d18fcec268e3ea1378b457e.html|title=La Quinta de Oro|trans-title=The Golden Fifth|date=30 June 2019|newspaper=Marca|language=es|access-date=16 April 2020}}</ref><ref name=u21bbc/>

===Senior===
Simón received his first call-up to [[Spain national football team|Spain senior team]] on 20 August 2020, for the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-lista-convocados-seleccion-espanola-partidos-uefa-nations-league-alemania-y-ucrania|title=Oficial: Lista de convocados de la Selección española para los partidos de la UEFA Nations League ante Alemania y Ucrania|trans-title=Official: List of called-up players by the Spain national team for the UEFA Nations League matches against Germany and Ukraine|publisher=[[Royal Spanish Football Federation]]|language=es|date=20 August 2020|access-date=20 August 2020|archive-date=30 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200830080056/https://www.sefutbol.com/oficial-lista-convocados-seleccion-espanola-partidos-uefa-nations-league-alemania-y-ucrania|url-status=dead}}</ref> Despite having made an error which led to a goal at club level a few days earlier, he debuted in a friendly match against [[Netherlands national football team|the Netherlands]] on 11 November, playing the entire match.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://athletic.elcorreo.com/unai-simon-debuta-seleccion-20201111195911-nt.html|title=Luis Enrique echa un capote a Simón|trans-title=Luis Enrique throws a cape on Simón|newspaper=[[El Correo]]|publisher=Bilbao Editorial|language=es|date=12 November 2020|access-date=12 November 2020}}</ref>

On 24 May 2021, Simón was included in [[Luis Enrique]]'s [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#Spain|24-man squad]] for [[UEFA Euro 2020]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Braidwood |first=Jamie |title=Euro 2020 News Live: Sergio Ramos left out of Spain squad plus latest before England announcement |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/euro-2020-news-live-england-squad-b1852654.html |access-date=17 July 2025|newspaper=The Independent |date=24 May 2021}}</ref> Having displaced [[David de Gea]] as first-choice, he started all of the team's matches, and caused an [[own goal]] in the 5–3 round of 16 victory against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] when he was unable to control a long backwards pass by [[Pedri]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=del Río |first=José |title=Unai Simon's horrific mistake for Croatia's opener |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/uefa-euro/2021/06/28/60da04b1268e3ebe3b8b459b.html |access-date=7 July 2021|newspaper=Marca|date=28 June 2021}}</ref> Luis Enrique praised his mentality for having recovered from that mistake.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Unai Simon and Pedri team up for shocking Spain own goal, but keeper gains 'redemption' |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57643907 |access-date=7 July 2021|website=BBC Sport|publisher=BBC|date=28 June 2021}}</ref> He eventually saved two penalties as Spain won the shootout against [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in the quarter-finals after a 1–1 draw,<ref name="Pueblo"/> for which he was also awarded the Star of the Match.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/history/news/026b-12a94a0fe9f1-c2503bc98c72-1000--spain-pip-swiss-on-penalties/ |title=Switzerland 1–1 Spain (pens: 1-3): La Roja pip Swiss on penalties to reach semi-finals |website=UEFA |date=2 July 2021 }}</ref> The semi-final against [[Italy national football team|Italy]] ended with the same score, and Simón saved the first attempt in the shootout by [[Manuel Locatelli]], but the Italians prevailed.<ref>{{cite news |title=Italy hold nerve to beat Spain on penalties and reach final |url=https://www.thehindu.com/sport/football/euro-2020-italy-hold-nerve-to-beat-spain-on-penalties-and-reach-final/article35182298.ece |access-date=7 July 2021|newspaper=The Hindu |date=6 July 2021}}</ref> Simón was also called up for the [[Spain national under-23 football team|Spanish Olympic team]] for the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|delayed 2020 tournament]] in Japan.<ref>{{Cite web|title=Pedri, Garcia & Torres among Spain's Euro 2020 players named in Tokyo Olympics squad |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/pedri-garcia-torres-among-spains-euro-2020-players-named-in/1c8y6858hfpia1xji4f8ej3pqi |access-date=7 July 2021|website=[[Goal (website)|Goal]]|publisher=Platform Group|date=29 June 2021}}</ref> With Simón as the starting goalkeeper they reached the final, but lost to [[Brazil national under-23 football team|Brazil]].<ref name="Oly2021">{{cite web|url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/15234/12375555/tokyo-2020-olympics-brazil-retain-olympic-football-gold-with-malcom-extra-time-winner|title=Tokyo 2020 Olympics: Brazil retain Olympic football gold with Malcom extra-time winner|website=[[Sky Sports]]|publisher=Sky Group|date = 8 August 2021|access-date=25 October 2021}}</ref>

Simón was the starter at the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]], in which Spain progressed from their group with a victory, draw, and defeat – before losing 3–0 on penalties to [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup knockout stage#Round of 16|round of 16]] after a goalless draw. He saved from [[Badr Benoun]], but the three of teammates failed with their efforts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/63789751|title=World Cup 2022: Morocco 0–0 Spain (3–0 pens) Achraf Hakimi chips winning penalty to reach quarters |first=Shamoon|last=Hafez|date=6 December 2022|website=BBC Sport|access-date=6 December 2022}}</ref> Spain had better fortune in the [[2023 UEFA Nations League final]] one year later, where another goalless draw against [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]] was followed by a 5–4 victory in the shootout to claim the title, Simón blocking attempts from [[Lovro Majer]] and [[Bruno Petković]].<ref name=":1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/live/2023/jun/18/croatia-v-spain-nations-league-final-live|title=Croatia 0–0 Spain (4–5 on pens), as it happened|newspaper=The Guardian|date=18 June 2023|access-date=20 June 2023}}</ref>

On 7 June 2024, Simón was named in Spain's squad for [[UEFA Euro 2024|European Championships the same year]]. He started and played all matches except the final group stage match. In the latter, Simón played the full 90 minutes of [[UEFA Euro 2024 final|the final]] as Spain beat England to become European champions for the fourth time.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cp68zzx8x4rt|title=England 1-2 Spain: Euro 2024 final heartbreak for England as late Spain goal secures fourth European Championship|website=BBC Sport|date=11 July 2024|access-date=17 July 2025}}</ref>

